Package: node-cli-truncate
Version: 1.1.0-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Debian Javascript Maintainers <pkg-javascript-devel@lists.alioth.debian.org>
Installed-Size: 17
Depends: nodejs, node-slice-ansi (>= 1.0.0), node-string-width (>= 2.0.0)
Section: javascript
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/sindresorhus/cli-truncate#readme
Description: Truncate a string to a specific width in the terminal
 Gracefully handles ANSI escapes. Like a string styled with chalk. It also
 supports Unicode surrogate pairs and fullwidth characters.
 .
 Node.js is an event-based server-side JavaScript engine.
